WorkItem.Description:
(This issue is related to [enum carrying data](https://typescript.codeplex.com/workitem/2584).)

I'd love to see switch-statements as powerful as pattern matching in functional languages. In these lanugages you can destruct the expression in the "case":

```
switch(an_array) {
  case null || undefined:
    // Hm
    break;
  case []:
    console.log("an empty array");
    break;
  case [x, y]:
    console.log("two elements, x = " + x + ", and y = " + y);  // Using x and y here from the case
    break;
  case [head, ...tail...]:  // Some proper syntax is needed to refer to the "tail" of the array
    console.log("length of array is 1 + " tail.length);
    break;
}
```

In the same way, if enums could carry any data:

```
switch (an_option):
  case None:
    // nothing here
    break;
  case Some x:
    console.log("We got " + x);
    break;
  default:
    // In the dream scenario, this won't be needed because of exhaustiveness checks on an_option (can only be None or Some)
    break;
```
